CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 3, 1950, pg. 28, reads: "Comedian Visits - While here with the Jack Benny troupe Monday night for a Syria Mosque appearance, the famous 'Rochester' took time out to visit with a Hill City group.  Left to right: Carl Redwood, assistant director, Hill City; Rochester himself, [illegible] Gary and James Henry Jr., Hill City [ill.] - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Carl Redwood Sr., Eddie "Rochester" Anderson, Ms. Gary, and James Henry Jr. shaking Anderson's hand
